  <!-- FAQ (visible) -->
  <section class="faq">
    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <h3>Is Double VPN the same as Tor?</h3>
    <p>No. Tor uses multiple independently run relays and distributes trust. Double VPN uses two hops within a single provider’s network — stronger than single-hop, but not Tor-level anonymity.</p>

    <h3>Will Double VPN bypass geo-blocks better?</h3>
    <p>Usually not. For region-locked services, pick a single nearby server with solid unblocking. See <a href="/en-us/blog/vpn-geo-blocks.html">geo-blocks & VPN</a>.</p>

    <h3>Can I use Double VPN for torrenting?</h3>
    <p>It works, but you’ll feel the speed loss. Prefer a single P2P-friendly server with leak protection enabled.</p>

    <h3>Which protocols are best?</h3>
    <p>Start with WireGuard/NordLynx for performance; fall back to OpenVPN (TCP) only on very restrictive networks.</p>
  </section>

